-- Shares in BPER suspended limit-down as cash call starts
-- 
-- Mon Jun 23, 2014 05:05AM EDT
-- None



MILAN, June 23 (Reuters) - Shares in Italy's Banca Popolare dell'Emilia Romagna (BPER) <EMII.MI> were suspended from trading on Monday after losing more than 5 percent in the first day of a 750 million euro ($1.02 billion) rights issue.

Rights to buy into the mid-sized lender's cash call were down 21 percent at 0900 GMT.